BitField.name: TIME_STAMP
BitField.description: Free-Running Counter Time stamp. This 16-bit field is a copy of the Free-Running Timer, captured for Tx and Rx frames at the time when the beginning of the Identifier field appears on the CAN bus.

BitField.name: DLC
BitField.description: Length of the data to be stored/transmitted.

BitField.name: RTR
BitField.description: Remote Transmission Request. One/zero for remote/data frame.

BitField.name: IDE
BitField.description: ID Extended. One/zero for extended/standard format frame.

BitField.name: SRR
BitField.description: Substitute Remote Request. Contains a fixed recessive bit.

BitField.name: CODE
BitField.description: Message Buffer Code. This 4-bit field can be accessed (read or write) by the CPU and by the FlexCAN module itself, as part of the message buffer matching and arbitration process.

BitField.name: ESI
BitField.description: Error State Indicator. This bit indicates if the transmitting node is error active or error passive.

BitField.name: BRS
BitField.description: Bit Rate Switch. This bit defines whether the bit rate is switched inside a CAN FD format frame.

BitField.name: EDL
BitField.description: Extended Data Length. This bit distinguishes between CAN format and CAN FD format frames. The EDL bit must not be set for Message Buffers configured to RANSWER with code field 0b1010.

Register.name: ID0
Register.description: Message Buffer 0 ID Register

BitField.name: EXT
BitField.description: Contains extended (LOW word) identifier of message buffer.

BitField.name: STD
BitField.description: Contains standard/extended (HIGH word) identifier of message buffer.

BitField.name: PRIO
BitField.description: Local priority. This 3-bit fieldis only used when LPRIO_EN bit is set in MCR and it only makes sense for Tx buffers. These bits are not transmitted. They are appended to the regular ID to define the transmission priority.

Register.name: CS16
Register.description: Message Buffer 16 CS Register

BitField.name: TIME_STAMP
BitField.description: Free-Running Counter Time stamp. This 16-bit field is a copy of the Free-Running Timer, captured for Tx and Rx frames at the time when the beginning of the Identifier field appears on the CAN bus.

BitField.name: DLC
BitField.description: Length of the data to be stored/transmitted.

BitField.name: RTR
BitField.description: Remote Transmission Request. One/zero for remote/data frame.

BitField.name: IDE
BitField.description: ID Extended. One/zero for extended/standard format frame.

BitField.name: SRR
BitField.description: Substitute Remote Request. Contains a fixed recessive bit.

BitField.name: CODE
BitField.description: Message Buffer Code. This 4-bit field can be accessed (read or write) by the CPU and by the FlexCAN module itself, as part of the message buffer matching and arbitration process.

BitField.name: ESI
BitField.description: Error State Indicator. This bit indicates if the transmitting node is error active or error passive.

BitField.name: BRS
BitField.description: Bit Rate Switch. This bit defines whether the bit rate is switched inside a CAN FD format frame.

BitField.name: EDL
BitField.description: Extended Data Length. This bit distinguishes between CAN format and CAN FD format frames. The EDL bit must not be set for Message Buffers configured to RANSWER with code field 0b1010.

Register.name: CS25
Register.description: Message Buffer 25 CS Register

BitField.name: TIME_STAMP
BitField.description: Free-Running Counter Time stamp. This 16-bit field is a copy of the Free-Running Timer, captured for Tx and Rx frames at the time when the beginning of the Identifier field appears on the CAN bus.

BitField.name: DLC
BitField.description: Length of the data to be stored/transmitted.

BitField.name: RTR
BitField.description: Remote Transmission Request. One/zero for remote/data frame.

BitField.name: IDE
BitField.description: ID Extended. One/zero for extended/standard format frame.

BitField.name: SRR
BitField.description: Substitute Remote Request. Contains a fixed recessive bit.

BitField.name: CODE
BitField.description: Message Buffer Code. This 4-bit field can be accessed (read or write) by the CPU and by the FlexCAN module itself, as part of the message buffer matching and arbitration process.

BitField.name: ESI
BitField.description: Error State Indicator. This bit indicates if the transmitting node is error active or error passive.

BitField.name: BRS
BitField.description: Bit Rate Switch. This bit defines whether the bit rate is switched inside a CAN FD format frame.

BitField.name: EDL
BitField.description: Extended Data Length. This bit distinguishes between CAN format and CAN FD format frames. The EDL bit must not be set for Message Buffers configured to RANSWER with code field 0b1010.

BitField.name: ADC0PRETRGSEL
BitField.description: ADC0 Pretrigger Select

Enum.description: Pre-trigger ADHDWTSA is selected, thus ADC0 will use ADC0_SC1A configuration for the next ADC conversion and store the result in ADC0_RA register.
Pre-trigger ADHDWTSB is selected, thus ADC0 will use ADC0_SC1B configuration for the next ADC conversion and store the result in ADC0_RB register.

BitField.name: ADC0ALTTRGEN
BitField.description: ADC0 Alternate Trigger Enable

Enum.description: ADC ADHWT trigger comes from TPM1 channel 0 and channel1. Prior to the assertion of TPM1 channel 0, a pre-trigger pulse will be sent to ADHWTSA to initiate an ADC acquisition using ADCx_SC1A configuration and store ADC conversion in ADCx_RA Register. Prior to the assertion of TPM1 channel 1 a pre-trigger pulse will be sent to ADHWTSB to initiate an ADC acquisition using ADCx_SC1Bconfiguration and store ADC conversion in ADCx_RB Register.

ADC ADHWT trigger comes from a peripheral event selected by ADC0TRGSEL bits.ADC0PRETRGSEL bit will select the optional ADHWTSA or ADHWTSB select lines for choosing the ADCx_SC1x config and ADCx_Rx result regsiter to store the ADC conversion.

BitField.name: TXCTSE
BitField.description: Transmitter clear-to-send enable

Enum.description: CTS has no effect on the transmitter.

Enables clear-to-send operation. The transmitter checks the state of CTS each time it is ready to send a character. If CTS is asserted, the character is sent. If CTS is deasserted, the signal TXD remains in the mark state and transmission is delayed until CTS is asserted. Changes in CTS as a character is being sent do not affect its transmission.

BitField.name: TXRTSE
BitField.description: Transmitter request-to-send enable

Enum.description: The transmitter has no effect on RTS.

When a character is placed into an empty transmitter data buffer , RTS asserts one bit time before the start bit is transmitted. RTS deasserts one bit time after all characters in the transmitter data buffer and shift register are completely sent, including the last stop bit.

BitField.name: TXCTSE
BitField.description: Transmitter clear-to-send enable

Enum.description: CTS has no effect on the transmitter.

Enables clear-to-send operation. The transmitter checks the state of CTS each time it is ready to send a character. If CTS is asserted, the character is sent. If CTS is deasserted, the signal TXD remains in the mark state and transmission is delayed until CTS is asserted. Changes in CTS as a character is being sent do not affect its transmission.

BitField.name: TXRTSE
BitField.description: Transmitter request-to-send enable

Enum.description: The transmitter has no effect on RTS.

When a character is placed into an empty transmitter data buffer , RTS asserts one bit time before the start bit is transmitted. RTS deasserts one bit time after all characters in the transmitter data buffer and shift register are completely sent, including the last stop bit.

BitField.name: DMAEN
BitField.description: DMA Enable

Enum.description: All DMA signalling disabled.

DMA transfer is enabled. While SMB[FACK] = 0, the following conditions trigger the DMA request: a data byte is received, and either address or data is transmitted. (ACK/NACK is automatic) the first byte received matches the A1 register or is a general call address. If any address matching occurs, S[IAAS] and S[TCF] are set. If the direction of transfer is known from master to slave, then it is not required to check S[SRW]. With this assumption, DMA can also be used in this case. In other cases, if the master reads data from the slave, then it is required to rewrite the C1 register operation. With this assumption, DMA cannot be used. When FACK = 1, an address or a data byte is transmitted.

BitField.name: DMAEN
BitField.description: DMA Enable

Enum.description: All DMA signalling disabled.

DMA transfer is enabled. While SMB[FACK] = 0, the following conditions trigger the DMA request: a data byte is received, and either address or data is transmitted. (ACK/NACK is automatic) the first byte received matches the A1 register or is a general call address. If any address matching occurs, S[IAAS] and S[TCF] are set. If the direction of transfer is known from master to slave, then it is not required to check S[SRW]. With this assumption, DMA can also be used in this case. In other cases, if the master reads data from the slave, then it is required to rewrite the C1 register operation. With this assumption, DMA cannot be used. When FACK = 1, an address or a data byte is transmitted.

Register.name: LR_AA_CFG
Register.description: PHY Long Range AA Config

BitField.name: AA_COR_THRESH
BitField.description: Threshold use to compare the correlation magnitude in the long-range AA correlator.

BitField.name: AA_HAM_THRESH
BitField.description: Threshold use to compare the Hamming distance, between reference coded sequence and received coded sequence, in the long-range AA correlator.

BitField.name: ACCESS_ADDR_HAM
BitField.description: Threshold use to compare the Hamming distance, between the reference AA sequence and the received Viterbi decoded AA sequence.

BitField.name: AA_LR_CORR_GAIN
BitField.description: AA correlator gain. Format ufix6en3. This gain is applied to soft bits from the demodulator before they are used for address search synchronization.

Register.name: LR_STAT
Register.description: PHY Long Range Status

BitField.name: DECODED_HAMM_DIST
BitField.description: Hamming distance between the reference sequence and the Viterbi decoded received sequence

BitField.name: AA_FOUND
BitField.description: Indicates that a AA detect is active for both LR and uncoded.

BitField.name: CI
BitField.description: CI received.

BitField.name: CODED_HAMM_DIST
BitField.description: Hamming distance between the coded reference sequence and the coded received sequence.

BitField.name: AA_CORR_MAX
BitField.description: Indicates the AA correlation magnitude witnessed when AA match occurred

BitField.name: CMAG_MAX
BitField.description: Indicates the maximum preamble correlation magnitude during preamble found

Register.name: SM_CFG
Register.description: PHY State Machine Config

BitField.name: ACQ_MODE
BitField.description: Acquisition mode for non-coded reception

Enum.description: Use preamble and verify a correlation peak, the synch at the symbol rate as symbol timing is established by the preamble acquisition
Use synch only (which may incorporate part of the preamble)
Use mainly the sync detection: Use a low threshold on the preamble detector and launch the synch detection only if the preamble has shown a recent peak

BitField.name: EN_PHY_SM_EXT_RST
BitField.description: Reserved, should keep 0.

BitField.name: AGC_FRZ_ON_PD_FOUND_ACQ1_LR
BitField.description: Specfies AGC freeze condition for non-coded acq.1 and Bluetooth LE long range.

Enum.description: AGC freeze on AA found.
AGC freeze asserted on PD found.

BitField.name: PH_BUFF_PTR_SYM
BitField.description: Phase buffer size to demodulator, long range only.

BitField.name: EARLY_PD_TIMEOUT
BitField.description: Time-out used to reset the AGC state-machine for the eventuality that an "PD found early" event occurs but it is not followed by an "PD found" event

BitField.name: AA_TIMEOUT_UNCODED
BitField.description: Time-out value for access address search for uncoded packets

Register.name: MISC
Register.description: PHY Misc Config

BitField.name: RSSI_CORR_TH
BitField.description: Threshold use to compare a correlation magnitude value, computed in the acquisition block, in order to determine the correlation flag value provided by the PHY to the LQI computation block. Format is ufix8_En8

BitField.name: DMA_PAGE_SEL
BitField.description: Select which DMA page is send out

Enum.description: Select DMA PAGE 0 for M3C with cfo;
Select DMA PAGE 1 for M3C with magnitude;
Select DMA PAGE 2 for un-coded;
Select DMA PAGE 3 for Long Range Preampble Detect;
Select DMA PAGE 4 for Long Range AA Detect;

BitField.name: ECO1_RSVD
BitField.description: Reserved. Must be programed as reset value 0.

BitField.name: PHY_CLK_CTRL
BitField.description: Enables various clock gating features. Bits are individually decoded, so any combination is allowable.

BitField.name: DTEST_MUX_EN
BitField.description: Reserved. Should be programed as reset value 0.

BitField.name: PHY_CLK_ON
BitField.description: Force PHY clock ON

Register.name: STAT0

BitField.name: PD_FOUND
